nodes.event: Scrubbing in for the ER shift, checking personal readiness.
Reviewing incoming patient charts, mental preparation for potential cases.
Organizing surgical instruments and supplies in the ER bay.
Overhead 'Code Red' page for massive hemorrhage in OR 3. Sprinting there.
Patient stabilized; assisting with final closure and dressing application.
Post-op debrief with attending surgeon and OR team.
Completing the operative report and associated terminal paperwork.
Years ago: sitting helpless in the waiting room during my father's emergency surgery.
Childhood memory: the first distinctive smell of antiseptic after a playground accident.
